==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Potlatch
<hw>Pot"latch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chinook
<ets>potlatch</ets>, <ets>pahtlatch</ets>, fr. Nootka
<ets>pahchilt</ets>, <ets>pachalt</ets>, a gift.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Among the Kwakiutl, Chimmesyan, and other Indians of the
northwestern coast of North America, a ceremonial distribution by a man
of gifts to his own and neighboring tribesmen, often, formerly, to his
own impoverishment. Feasting, dancing, and public ceremonies accompany
it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, a feast given to a large number of persons,
often accompanied by gifts.</def> <mark>[Colloq., Northwestern
America]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pot lead</ent>⟦br⟧
